Media feature - @ndtveducation details the Smart India Hackathon grand finale with #IITKanpur being one of the nodal centres.

https://t.co/pEDMcesckk

#IITKanpur is proud to be one of the nodal centers to facilitate the SIH Software edition. 27 teams having 150 participants are competing against 27 problem statements from 23 organizations where prizes of Rs. 1 lakh, Rs. 75000, & Rs. 50000 will be provided to the winning teams.

Smart India Hackathon 2022 is jointly organized by the @mhrd_innovation, @AICTE_INDIA, @Persistentsys & @i4CIndia. @DDNational @ @AkashvaniAIR are the media partners, while @Shell, and @awscloud are the sponsoring partners.

Hon’ble Prime Minister of India, Shri @narendramodi Ji, has been interacting with the student participants of the Smart India Hackathon every year since its inception and is expected to interact with the students this year again on the evening of 25th August 2022. @PMOIndia

SIH 2022 has offered 476 problem statements received from 62 organizations. 2033 winner teams of campus level hackathons organized under Smart India Hackathon 2022, comprising more than 15000 students will participate in this year’s SIH grand finale at the national level.

Smart India Hackathon, a nationwide initiative by the @EduMinOfIndia’s Innovation Cell to provide students a platform to solve the pressing problems of  government, ministries, departments, industries etc, has its Hardware grand finale from 25-29 Aug & Software from 25-26 Aug. https://t.co/2owxElaHJj
